This paper proposes a method for compressing deep neural networks for computer vision applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the method involves regularization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves reducing the precision of the weights, which suggests that it may be relevant to the numerical optimization (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
